author: RTÉ News
title: China lockdown 'may have blocked 700,000 virus cases'
description: China's decision to lock down the city of Wuhan may have prevented more than 700,000 new cases by delaying the spread of the virus.
content:
China's decision to lock down the city of Wuhan, ground zero for the global COVID-19 pandemic, may have prevented more than 700,000 new cases by delaying the spread of the virus.
